      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WAGYU BOY (4) produced a modest effort most recently when sixth at this track over 450m behind Heroic Federer (25.55) in a Grade 5. Solid beginner who can clear the tricky draw. Has ability and is a key runner. ZIPPY TIPPY (8) turned in a better effort at this track last start, finishing third behind Blow Bayou (25.78) in a Grade 5. Turned chasing the leaders but kept coming. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Expected to be in the finish again. EPIFANIO (1) was among the minors three back at this track then missed the frame the last two, but drawn box 1 this time where he has two wins. Safe beginner and drawn well on the inside. This looks easier and expected to improve sharply.",
